OL,3,C'Corridor care crisis' - Nurse lifts
OL,4,Clid on hospital frontline services
OL,6,FThe Royal College of Nursing,
OL,7,Ffollowing the release of their report,
OL,8,Fhas called for immediate Government
OL,9,Faction to end 'corridor care', which
OL,10,Fit says has become normalised and is
OL,11,Fnot just occurring in the winter
OL,12,Fmonths.
OL,14,FIts chief executive Professor Nicola
OL,15,FRanger said winter pressures must not
OL,16,Fbe used as an excuse for ongoing
OL,17,Fcorridor care, and said the NHS does
OL,18,Fnot have enough staff or beds.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/5
